name: WestJet 737-7CT [C-GQWJ] "Tartan Tail" Taxiing at Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Aye, laddie! Here we have WestJet's newest special livery, AKA Tartan Tail, taxiing after landing at Calgary International Airport. Revealed on May 9th, to celebrate the addition of Glasgow to WestJet's route network, one of its first flights was YYC, and I just so happened to be out there when it returned from YMM, after flying there earlier in the day. Sorry for the shakiness, this was all filmed hand held, and you know me and hand held filming. I hope you enjoy this quick shot of Tartan Tail, nonetheless!

Thanks for watching! Please comment, rate, and subscribe!
